item.title: Earthquake rocks city in southern Taiwan
item.description: A powerful 6.4-magnitude earthquake hit Taiwan's oldest city of Tainan, toppling buildings, wounding hundreds and killing dozens of people. CNN's Azadeh Ansari reports.

item.title: China under pressure to rein in North Korea
item.description: North Korea's only ally, China, is being urged to use its influence to rein in the Hermit Kingdom. CNN's Michael Holmes talks to the director of the Korea-Pacific program at UCSD about events on the peninsula.

item.title: Strategist: Millennial women face different issues
item.description: Democratic strategist Nomiki Konst tells CNN's Fredricka Whitfield there's a generational disconnect between feminist leaders and millennial women when it comes to issues like economic inequality.

item.title: How the primary affects New Hampshire residents
item.description: In New Hampshire, the upcoming primary is part of everybody's life. One resident, a glass blower, shares how politics is making an impact.

item.title: Pirlo wants to play for Italy at EURO 16
item.description: The New York City FC midfielder hasn't given up hope of playing for his country at this year's European championships. He speaks with CNN's Kate Riley.

item.title: Can a fortune teller reveal the next U.S. President?
item.description: A fortune teller in Hong Kong tells CNN's Alexandra Field her projections about the next U.S. presidential election.

item.title: Cars fall into lake during winter festival
item.description: Cars parked on a frozen lake in Lake Geneva, Wisconsin, broke through the ice, causing them to fall into the water below. CNN affiliate WTMJ has the story.

item.title: The Obamas talk Super Bowl Sunday
item.description: President Barack Obama and first lady Michelle Obama sat down with CBS to discuss their Super Bowl Sunday at the White House. CNN's Poppy Harlow has more.

item.title: Year of the Monkey to bring new technology ideas?
item.description: Chinese traditions of the New Year are complicated, as explained in an interview CNN's Michael Holmes conducts with astrologer and Feng Shui consultant Ting-Foon Chik.

item.title: UN Security Council condemns North Korea launch
item.description: The United Nations Security Council held an unusual Sunday meeting to discuss how to deal with North Korea's rocket launch. CNN's Michael Holmes speaks with the South Korean ambassador to the UN.

item.title: Trump: 'Wouldn't be happy' with second place in N.H.
item.description: CNN's Dana Bash speaks with Donald Trump about his expectations before the New Hampshire primary.

item.title: Police: 2 dead in Orlando nightclub shooting
item.description: Orlando Police Department Public Information Officer Michelle Guido speaks to the media regarding a recent shooting at an Orlando nightclub.

item.title: Clinton's narrow Iowa caucus win confirmed
item.description: CNN's Jeff Zeleny and Fredricka Whitfield discuss the recent confirmation of Hillary Clinton's narrow Iowa caucus win.

item.title: Steinem apologizes for female Sanders supporters remark
item.description: Gloria Steinem apologized for comments she made on "Real Time with Bill Maher," suggesting some young women support Bernie Sanders to meet boys.

item.title: Jeb Bush: 'Donald Trump, you're the loser'
item.description: Presidential candidate Jeb Bush strongly attacks Donald Trump's past statements, and calls him a 'loser.'

item.title: CNN Student News - 2/8/16
item.description: Cereal is front and center on today's special edition of CNN Student News. Find out how the industry has changed and what influence consumers have on it.

item.title: Granholm: This is about basic human needs
item.description: Former Michigan Governor Jennifer Granholm speaks to CNN's Fredricka Whitfield about the water crisis in Flint, Michigan.

item.title: 2 teens killed sledding on closed Olympic track
item.description: Two brothers were killed after they and a group of friends apparently went down an Olympic bobsledding course on a personal sled, according to Canadian authorities.

item.title: How has the presidential race changed these candidates?
item.description: CNN's Jake Tapper asks presidential candidates Donald Trump, Sen. Bernie Sanders, Hillary Clinton, Gov. John Kasich, and Gov. Chris Christie how the race has changed them.

item.title: Moonves says NFL is 'best product on TV'
item.description: Brian Stelter asks CBS boss Les Moonves about Super Bowl coverage; $5 million ads; Stephen Colbert's post-game show; how CBS journalists cover the NFL; and much more.

item.title: Security beefed up before Super Bowl 50
item.description: A look at the unprecedented level of security for Superbowl 50 in the San Francisco Bay Area. CNN's Dan Simon reports.

item.title: Officials: Airport workers seen with explosive laptop
item.description: The man sucked out of a Somali airliner after an inflight explosion has been identified as Abdullahi Abdisalam Borleh, an elderly Somali national,officials said.

item.title: Slanted coverage of Clinton and Sanders?
item.description: Authors Rebecca Traister and Harry Jaffe dissect "roller coaster" media coverage of the Democratic presidential primary.

item.title: Why you should be skeptical about polls
item.description: Famed Iowa researcher J. Ann Selzer explains how viewers should interpret political polls and why polls are becoming harder and harder to conduct.

item.title: What caused ABC's debate intro disaster
item.description: Ana Marie Cox, Matt Lewis, and Rick Wilson discuss the awkward beginning of ABC's GOP debate; the big ratings; and the changing narrative about Marco Rubio.
